<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1668,2017]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Orange yellow with dark brown markings on disc of crown. Thorax and forewings as in 
<figureCitation box="[1147,1275,1668,1693]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[214,1399,234,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[161,1436,193,1893]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 2 A–R. Species of Evacanthini, habitus: A–B. Male Evacanthus bellus (Distant).; C–D. Male E. convolutus sp. nov.; E–F. Male E.. distinctus sp. nov,; G–H. Male E. manaliensis sp. nov.; I–J. Female E. militaris (Distant); K–L. Male E. yeshwanthi sp. nov.; M–N. Male Mainda praeculta Distant; O–P. Male Onukia echina sp. nov.; Q–R. Male O. flavopunctata Wang &amp; Li. [A, C, E, G, I, K, M, O, Q, dorsal views; B.D, F, H, J, L, N, P, R, lateral views]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1195890/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 2 O–P</figureCitation>
. Face thoracic pleura, sterna and legs without dark brown markings.
</paragraph>
