<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,295,320]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can at once be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Metcalf" authorityYear="1939" box="[1121,1272,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Evacanthinae">Evacanthinae</taxonomicName>
found in the subcontinent by its characteristic coloration in addition to the structure of the pygofer and aedeagus.
</paragraph>
